codex
The new section functions also need the downstream compiler’s existing motif/rhythm maps, otherwise new names degrade to generic behavior. I’m making a small compatibility patch: canonical scene names stay available, and the compiler maps the new function names to the same kinds of musical roles the older names had.
apply patch
